   <conbody>
      <div platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">In <ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">an uninterruptible
power supply (UPS)</ph>
            <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">a charger</ph> a rectifier
converts alternating current (AC) from the rectifier mains to direct
current (DC). The DC circuit <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">supplies the load
and </ph>charges the battery bank.<ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph "> The inverter
converts back DC to AC that supplies the load.</ph> If the rectifier
mains becomes unavailable, the load is supplied without interruption
by the battery bank.</p>
         <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">A system without a bypass
can for example be used as a frequency converter. With this configuration
no bypass operation or manual bypass is available.</p>
         <fig platform="SDC" class="- topic/fig ">
            <image href="../Images/FD_SDC_Configuration-Options_Single_0000517612.svg"
                   placement="inline"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
         <fig platform="PxW" class="- topic/fig ">
            <image href="../Images/FD_PxW_Configuration-Options_Basic_Functionality_0000348395.svg"
                   placement="inline"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </div>
      <div platform="WxW" class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">In an inverter system an inverter converts
direct current (DC) to alternating current (AC) that supplies the
load.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">A system without a bypass can for example be used together
with a DC UPS system as a frequency converter. With this configuration
there is no alternative supply for the load.</p>
